Nadal beat Federer in straight sets in Rome
2013-05-20 01:19:13 GMT
Rafael Nadal achieved an unexpectedlyeasy win over Roger Federer in their 30th clash as the Spaniardbagged his seventh Rome Masters title on Sunday.Fifth seed Nadal used just an hour and eight minutes to beatFederer 6-1, 6-3, moving 20-10 against the Swiss and 13-2 on theclay surface.Federer committed 32 unforced errors and managed just one breakfrom Nadal who forced six break points and took five of them.With the win in Rome, Nadal has won three straight tournamenttitles, a perfect preparation for the upcoming French Open.Serena Williams won her fourth consecutive tournament victorywhen she beat Victoria Azarenka 6-1, 6-3 in the women's final,extending her unbeaten run to 24 matches.The American, 31, will head to Paris as a strong favorite to winthe title at Roland Garros for only the second time.Her victory at the Foro Italico on Sunday followed wins inMiami, South Carolina and Madrid. Enditem
